<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 26 at 10:57PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light snow overnight...
Scattered snow showers will affect areas around MacDonald Pass,
Boulder Pass, Elk Park Pass and the Helena area overnight.
New snow accumulations of 1 to 2 inches will be possible in the
mountains, while up to a half inch is possible at lower
elevations.
Visibility could fall below one mile at times, with winds gusting
near 30 mph on mountain passes.
Those traveling through this region overnight should be prepared
for quickly changing road conditions along with areas of poor
driving visibility.</description>
